    {
      "type": "grammar_spotlight",
      "content": "Look at the phrase <ruby>越<rt>こ</rt></ruby>えした (koeshita). The verb is 'koe' (cross). By adding 'ta', the poet isn't just saying they were crossing; they are saying the crossing is *behind them*. The 'ni' (at/when) that follows marks the specific moment *after* the completion. \n\nLogic: [Action: Cross] + [Status: Completed (た)] + [Time: When (に)] = 'At the moment I had finished crossing...'",
      "evidence": "See the poem above."
    },
